channel.title: Help port forward
channel.description:
I have a server and I'm trying to host another with a different port and I've forwarded
[b]THIS IS MY ROUTER PORT FORWARD[/b] [code]Port Range Application-Start---------End--Protocol-IPAddress server----55555---to---55555---Both---192.168.*.**---Enable[/code] This is my port forward, and its right because I did the same thing for my other server And, yes I remembered to change the port[code]public static int serverlistenerPort = 55555; //43594=default[/code] Yes, I'm compiling. Yes, I've forwared through my firewall, even tried turning it off. Yet it still doesnt work, any ideas?

…thats exactly what this is Port Range Application-Start---------End--Protocol-IPAddress server----55555---to---55555---Both---192.168.*.**---Enable thats me forwarding on my router, and I took my IP out on purpose.

I’ve forwarded on my router, my firewall, and even freaking windows firewall which is disabled…double and triple checked I did it right, and typed the port correctly, yet It still wont work, and I forwarded no-ips port 80. (I have it set to use 80 and not its default)

anyone?

item.title: Help port forward
item.dc:creator: @Frell Frell
item.description:
@Frell wrote:

Ok,

you know this part:

192.168.*.**---Enable

Go to:
start > run > cmd > type ipconfig.

You use you default gateway to connect to your router online,

you ip address is what you put right here:

192.168.*.**---Enable

EDIT: Oh, you got it.
